Deji Elumoye in Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari is about now meeting with members of the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) at the State House, Abuja over the proposed National Convention of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). PGF is made up of governors elected on the platform of the ruling APC. The governors are being led to the meeting by their Chairman and Governor of Kebbi State, Atiku Bagudu, and the Chairman of the Nigeria Governors’ Forum (NGF), Dr Kayode Fayemi, with the Chairman of the Interim Committee of the APC and Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni, also in attendance. The PGF is expected to brief the president on the outcome of its Monday evening meeting during which March 26, 2022 was fixed as the new date to hold the party’s national convention. The meeting is expected to get the approval of President Buhari for the March 26 date in his capacity as the national leader of the party. Details later…